From 14efab4d45aaaa03505966b97e0b294ef46461a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 15:25:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 09/27] B4b cleanup: strip bring-up diagnostics + drop the dead
 weave_target plumbing (#625)

Post-eyeball cleanup of the B4b per-element inline-3D weave (CEF sub-rect model).
Weave re-verified firing end-to-end after the removal (service leia_dp_d3d11_
process_atlas weave lines, browser bindWindow -> 0).

Strip: all bring-up LOG diagnostics + the one-shot BGRA dump (+ its Sk includes)
across skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc, xr_session.cc, xr_frame_provider.cc,
display.cc, layer_tree_host_impl.cc, surface_aggregator.cc, and the CFM traits.
Kept the error-only logs (woven import / WeavePixels failures).

Drop the now-dead B3a Seam-A/B weave_target tag path (the CEF sub-rect model
reads the composited output sub-rect via CompositorFrameMetadata::inline_3d_rects
instead of tagging a per-canvas quad, which Windows chrome never produces):
- Blink: HTMLCanvasElement::SetInline3D + inline_3d_ + the TextureLayer::
  SetWeaveTarget wiring; XRDisplayLayer now only registers/deregisters with the
  session (no canvas tag).
- cc: TextureLayer / TextureLayerImpl weave_target_ + SetWeaveTarget + the
  quad stamp + the pending->active propagation.
- viz: TextureDrawQuad::weave_target; quads.mojom weave_target + traits;
  ExternalUseClient::ImageContext is_weave_target/weave_rect + members;
  SkiaRenderer's tag bridge + DisplayXRInline3DEnabled; ImageContextImpl's
  SetWeaveOverrideMailbox + weave_override_mailbox_/weave_produced_mailbox_ +
  the fulfillment override.
- gpu: SharedImageManager/RepresentationFactory::ProduceOverlayForWeave (the
  readback path no longer needs a D3D-texture overlay of the canvas).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
